SIMPLE: moralist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moralist
<hw>Mor"al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>moraliste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who moralizes; one who
teaches or animadverts upon the duties of life; a writer of essays
intended to correct vice and inculcate moral duties.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who practices moral duties; a person who lives
in conformity with moral rules; one of correct deportment and dealings
with his fellow-creatures; -- sometimes used in contradistinction to one
whose life is controlled by religious motives.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The love (in the <qex>moralist</qex> of virtue, but in the
Christian) of God himself.</q> <rj><qau>Hammond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>moralistic</ent>⟦br⟧
